  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dae\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dbb \u0dad\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dca\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd4 - \u0dab\u0dba \u0db4\u0dc4\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0db8\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dbd \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dd3 \u0d85\u0db1\u0dd4\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dad \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Fixed Deposits \u2013 Increases interest rates on credit facilities",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Taking into account the current and expected macroeconomic developments in Sri Lanka, the Monetary Board of the Central Bank of Sri Lanka decided to raise interest rates on fixed deposits and credit facilities in a meeting held yesterday (06), the Central Bank announced today (07) in a statement.",
        "The Central Bank's Monetary Board has decided to raise the Fixed Deposit Facility Rate and Fixed Credit Facility Rate by 100 basis points, 14.50 percent and 15.50 percent respectively.",
        "Also, according to the statement issued by the Central Bank, the Monetary Board has decided to maintain the statutory reserve ratio at the current level of 4 percent."
      ],
